entry.title: Russia Tightens Grip Around Bakhmut as Ukraine Awaits Western Tanks
entry.content: Kyiv urged the West to provide longer-range firepower to counter Russia’s missile barrages as Russia’s invasion forces tightened the noose around the beleaguered eastern city.

entry.title: Some Western Backers of Ukraine Worry That Time Might Be on Russia's Side
entry.content: Officials in some capitals fear the Kremlin, which is willing to keep throwing men and materiel into the war, could gain the upper hand in any lengthy war of attrition.
